íŸ@0c6f3437b84c359ceefe3a208c1e3005885cf50be319d455d592a830108bf4f6⁄ØTitle: title: run-external
Path: Examples
Content:
Run an external command
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> run-external "echo" "-n" "hello"


```
Redirect stdout from an external command into the pipeline
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> run-external "echo" "-n" "hello" | split chars


```
Redirect stderr from an external command into the pipeline
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> run-external "nu" "-c" "print -e hello" e>| split chars


```
íŸ@f9dd3bc5f44bd39fa96269cfb0ae9f59d2d302e16e20b5f6be0a68657bf5e80f⁄Title: title: run-external
Path: Notes
Content:
All externals are run with this command, whether you call it directly with 
``run-external external``
 or use 
``external``
 or 
``^external``
.

If you create a custom command with this name, that will be used instead.
